            . I am shopman to Mary Colls, who is a <rs id="t18200217-8-viclabel45" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200217-8-victim128 t18200217-8-viclabel45"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18200217-8-crimeloc46">Grace's-alley, Whitechapel</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200217-8-crimeloc46" type="placeName" value="Grace's-alley, Whitechapel"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200217-8-crimeloc46" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200217-8-off43 t18200217-8-crimeloc46"></join>. On the 11th of February the prisoner came to the shop with another woman, and looked at some prints - none would suit them. I saw the prisoner take the piece of sarsnet out of the window, put it on a chair, and conceal it under her clothes. I followed her out of the shop, brought her back, and took it from her - it cost 49 s.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I did not take it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200217-8-verdict47" type="verdictDescription">
